rtld-dispatch
=============

rtld-dispatch is a custom build of the GNU C Library's dynamic linker (ld.so).

The final ld.so link is driven by cargo (nix-ld style): glibc is built only up to
`librtld.os`, then a `bin` crate links that (rtld = the libc subset + the `_start`
entry) together with our `claude_dispatch` hook into the ld.so.

What this repository contains:
  - glibc/rtld-dispatch.patch — a small patch to glibc's elf/rtld.c (the dl_main hook).
                           No elf/Makefile change: the final link is ours, not glibc's.
  - src/                 — a no_std `bin` crate; src/main.rs is the `claude_dispatch`
                           hook (no main/_start of its own — rtld provides _start).
  - build.rs             — drives the whole build: extracts/patches/configures/makes
                           glibc → librtld.os, then injects glibc's ld.so link recipe
                           + librtld.os so cargo's own link produces the ld.so.
  - .cargo/config.toml   — selects gcc/bfd (not rust-lld) for the final link.
  - Makefile             — build + `patchelf --remove-rpath` + install as <prog>.rtld
                           (the rpath strip can't live in build.rs — it runs pre-link).
  - glibc/glibc-*.tar.xz — pristine upstream glibc source (Git LFS), unmodified.
  - glibc/slackware/     — Slackware's glibc patches + SlackBuild, for reference.
  - patch_agy_wsl1.py    — standalone (unrelated to the ld.so build): patches Google's
                           Antigravity CLI binary so its bundled tcmalloc runs on WSL1.

